{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"63ee43b7-7a36-4757-b473-9bea8de94a34","content":"Use the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nOr filter by class name directly:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter ClassName=ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nIf you need to specify the project too:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test TestProject.csproj --filter ClassName=ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", so `FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests` matches any test whose fully qualified name includes that string. The `=` operator requires an exact match on the class name.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"67258b05-c1fb-4ce9-b14d-6665ea2c95d1","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to know how to run only a specific test class using `dotnet test`. This is a straightforward question I can answer directly.","outputTokens":198,"requestId":"7028:20D09C:B548C0:D23C62:69F2AE49"},"id":"a5273938-ed72-4095-90fb-24d783c0e6b0","timestamp":"2026-04-30T01:20:14.119Z","parentId":"4398360e-1f16-440f-877c-71fb16f6eba1"}
